<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="vital-adj">vital <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'vaɪtl/    美 /'vaɪtl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>至关重要的</strong></h4>
<p>very important or necessary (essential)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>What’s worse, some drivers do not think it vital to obey traffi c rules.
更糟糕的是，一些司机不认为遵守交通规则是极为重要的。</p><footer>2015 江苏书面表达改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>of vital importance</strong>(= very important)
至关重要</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Consideration for other people is <strong>vital to</strong> all of us.
对我们所有人来说，体谅他人至关重要。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If the injuries are second or third degree burns, <strong>it is vital to get</strong> the victim to the doctor or hospital at once.
如果是二级或三级烧伤，那么立刻带伤者去看医生或者去医院是性命攸关的事。</p><footer>人教⑤ – 5</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Interest is as vital to<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (learn) as the ability to understand, even more so.  （2012 安徽改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. learning  </p></div>